# Failure Scenarios — IaC Identity & Provisioning

## Scope

Covers failure cases observed during:

* OpenTofu provisioning
* Ansible identity configuration
* Initial network setup

---

## Purpose

* Document real-world failure modes
* Improve troubleshooting speed
* Build a security-oriented mindset (assume failure/misconfiguration)

---

# Scenario 1 — Proxmox Authentication Timeout

## Error

```bash
Failed to authenticate: context deadline exceeded
```

## Cause

* Temporary connectivity issue to Proxmox API
* Possible DNS/network instability

## Impact

* OpenTofu unable to provision VM
* Deployment halted

## Resolution

* Re-run `tofu apply`

## Prevention

* Validate API reachability before apply:

```bash
curl https://<proxmox-api>
```

---

# Scenario 2 — Disk Resize Failure

## Error

```bash
Requested size (20G) is lower than current size (60G)
```

## Cause

* Template disk size larger than requested size
* OpenTofu cannot shrink disks

## Impact

* VM creation failed

## Resolution

* Match disk size with template (60G)

## Prevention

* Inspect template before defining resources
* Treat templates as baseline constraints

---

# Scenario 3 — Ansible Privilege Escalation Failure

## Error

```bash
Missing sudo password
```

## Cause

* Playbook requires root privileges
* No become password provided

## Impact

* Playbook execution failed

## Resolution

```bash
ansible-playbook ... -K
```

## Prevention

* Always include `-K` when using `become: true`
* Consider SSH key + passwordless sudo (future improvement)

