# Scenario 6 — Multiple Hosts with Same IP

## Symptom

* Ansible behaves unpredictably
* Wrong host gets configured

## Cause

* Cloned VMs share same IP
* Playbook executed against multiple hosts

## Impact

* Network conflicts
* Configuration drift

## Resolution

* Use:

```bash
--limit <host>
```

* Configure hosts one-by-one

## Prevention

* Never run playbooks on duplicated IP environments
* Ensure unique identity before scaling

---

# Scenario 7 — Loss of Connectivity After Netplan Apply

## Symptom

* SSH session drops after playbook run

## Cause

* IP address changed during execution

## Impact

* Temporary loss of management access

## Resolution

* Reconnect using new IP:

```bash
ssh user@<new-ip>
```

## Prevention

* Be aware of state transition:

  * `ansible_host` ≠ `ip_address`
* Validate new IP immediately after change

---

# Scenario 8 — Host Unreachable by Ansible

## Error

```bash
UNREACHABLE!
```

## Cause

* No network route
* Wrong subnet
* Firewall blocking SSH

## Impact

* Playbook cannot execute

## Resolution

* Verify:

```bash
ping <host>
ssh user@<host>
```

## Prevention

* Always perform connectivity test:

```bash
ansible all -m ping --limit <host>
```

